The paper discusses the design, implementation, and evaluation of a distributed deep learning framework, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). However, the focus of the paper is on deep learning, which suggests that it could also belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
